article.headline: W. Illinois 35, Jacksonville 21
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Josh Hudson threw three touchdown passes to lead Western Illinois past Jacksonville 35-21 on Saturday. Hudson was 14 of 20 for 205 yards for Western Illinois (1-1). His 54-yard touchdown pass to Terriun Crump with 2:33 to play finished the scoring. Crump caught seven passes for 143 yards. Caulton Ray ran for 118 yards, including a 54-yard TD for the Leathernecks. Josh McGregor's third touchdown pass, a 46-yarder to Quintin Davis, tied the game at 21 late in the third quarter for the Dolphins (0-2). But Hudson hooked up with Myles Daughtry for a 24-yard score with 1 second remaining in the quarter to give the Leathernecks the lead for good.
